## Context
Follow-up to 0161 (audit + frozen-data policy C). The audit chose to keep the v1
figures frozen and disclose the appendix diagnostics as current-corpus robustness
(PR #907, `docs/audit-manuscript-stat-provenance.md`). The disclosure prose and the
`.gitignore` exception landed autonomously. What remains needs a pipeline run against
the corpus and so is deferred to the author's machine flow — and best done once the
in-progress v1.1.2 GROBID reference-extraction corpus is frozen, so the archived
numbers do not immediately go stale.

## Relevant files
- `content/manuscript.qmd` — A.5 prose numbers (84 nodes / 369 edges / share 0.89 /
  null 0.37 / z≈25) transcribed at line ~276; A.3 nine clustering numbers ~256–260.
- `scripts/compute_null_separation.py`, `scripts/plot_fig_traditions.py` — A.5 generator
  (builder A) + its co-citation graph; `separation.mk` target `make separation`.
- `scripts/compute_temporal_communities.py`, `content/_includes/cocitation-communities.md`
  — builder B (reports the conflicting 169 / 1,056 pre-2007 graph).
- `content/_includes/clustering-comparison.md` — stale, AI-generated A.3 source.
- `content/tables/tab_null_separation_pre2007.csv`, `tab_pre2007_coverage.csv` — now
  un-ignored (PR #907), awaiting generation + commit.

## Actions
1. On the frozen v1.1.2 corpus, `make separation`; commit
   `tab_null_separation_pre2007.csv` (+ coverage). Verify the A.5 prose numbers match
   the committed CSV; fix any drift in `manuscript.qmd`.
2. Reconcile the pre-2007 co-citation graph: run builder A and builder B on the *same*
   frozen `refined_citations` and diff node/edge counts. If they agree, it was
   citation-snapshot drift — cite one construction and note it. If they still disagree
   ~2×, it is a code bug (two canonical graphs) — fix and cite one.
3. Regenerate `clustering-comparison.md` (`compute_clustering_comparison`); re-check the
   nine A.3 numbers against the fresh include; drop the STALE/AI-generated warnings once
   human-reviewed.

## Test
- `content/tables/tab_null_separation_pre2007.csv` exists, is committed, and its values
  equal the A.5 prose numbers (red first: assert the CSV row matches the cited figures).

